-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                       G S U K 2 6 V   R E L E A S E
              AUTOMATED XMIT PACKAGING VIA GITHUB ACTIONS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
REPO    : https://github.com/wizardofzos/GSUKV26
PURPOSE : DEMONSTRATE AUTOMATED Z/OS XMIT BUILDS FROM A GITHUB REPOSITORY
FORMAT  : SEQUENTIAL FILE  LRECL=79  RECFM=F
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                         1. WHAT DOES THIS REPO DO
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

EVERY PUSH TO THE MASTER BRANCH TRIGGERS AN AUTOMATED BUILD THAT:

  1. COMPUTES THE NEXT VERSION TAG (E.G. V1.0 -> V1.1 -> V1.2)
  2. CREATES AND PUSHES THAT TAG TO GITHUB
  3. PACKAGES THE PDS FOLDER INTO A STANDARD Z/OS XMIT FILE
  4. PUBLISHES A GITHUB RELEASE WITH THE XMIT AS A DOWNLOADABLE ASSET

NO MANUAL TAGGING REQUIRED AFTER THE INITIAL V1.0.
TO BUMP THE MAJOR VERSION (E.G. V2.0), CREATE THAT TAG MANUALLY IN GITHUB.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                      2. WORKFLOW: .GITHUB/WORKFLOWS/PROCESS.YML
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TRIGGER:
  ON: PUSH TO BRANCH MASTER

  ANY COMMIT PUSHED TO MASTER AUTOMATICALLY STARTS THE PIPELINE.
  NO MANUAL INTERVENTION OR TAG CREATION NEEDED.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 1 OF 7 - CHECKOUT
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  ACTION  : ACTIONS/CHECKOUT@V6
  OPTION  : FETCH-DEPTH: 0

  CLONES THE FULL REPOSITORY INCLUDING ALL TAGS AND HISTORY.
  FETCH-DEPTH 0 IS REQUIRED SO THAT THE NEXT STEP CAN SEE ALL EXISTING
  VERSION TAGS. WITHOUT IT, GIT TAG WOULD RETURN NOTHING AND THE VERSION
  LOGIC WOULD ALWAYS RESET TO V1.0.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 2 OF 7 - COMPUTE NEXT VERSION
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  SHELL SCRIPT EMBEDDED IN THE WORKFLOW (BASH).
  OUTPUT: STEPS.VERSION.OUTPUTS.TAG  (E.G. V1.3)

  HOW IT WORKS:

    1. LIST ALL TAGS MATCHING V<MAJOR>.<MINOR> SORTED NEWEST FIRST:
         GIT TAG --LIST 'V*.*' --SORT=-VERSION:REFNAME | HEAD -N 1

    2. IF NO TAG EXISTS -> USE V1.0 AS THE STARTING POINT.

    3. IF A TAG EXISTS (E.G. V1.2):
         SPLIT ON '.' TO GET MAJOR=1 AND MINOR=2
         ADD 1 TO MINOR -> NEXT TAG = V1.3

    4. WRITE THE RESULT TO GITHUB_OUTPUT SO LATER STEPS CAN USE IT:
         ECHO "TAG=V1.3" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 3 OF 7 - CREATE AND PUSH TAG
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  CONFIGURES THE GIT USER AS GITHUB-ACTIONS[BOT] SO THE COMMIT AUTHOR
  SHOWS AS THE AUTOMATION ACCOUNT RATHER THAN A REAL USER.

  THEN:
    GIT TAG V1.3
    GIT PUSH ORIGIN V1.3

  THIS IS WHAT MAKES THE RELEASE APPEAR AS A PROPER TAGGED VERSION IN THE
  GITHUB REPOSITORY. THE TAG VALUE COMES FROM STEP 2 VIA:
    ${{ STEPS.VERSION.OUTPUTS.TAG }}

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 4 OF 7 - SET UP PYTHON 3.11
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  ACTION  : ACTIONS/SETUP-PYTHON@V5
  VERSION : 3.11

  INSTALLS A CLEAN PYTHON 3.11 RUNTIME ON THE UBUNTU RUNNER.
  REQUIRED BECAUSE THE XMIT GENERATION SCRIPT IS WRITTEN IN PYTHON.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 5 OF 7 - INSTALL DEPENDENCIES
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  UPGRADES PIP TO THE LATEST VERSION THEN INSTALLS:
    XMI-READER  - PYTHON LIBRARY FOR READING AND CREATING Z/OS XMIT FILES

  SEE: HTTPS://XMI.READTHEDOCS.IO

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 6 OF 7 - GENERATE XMIT
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  RUNS: PYTHON .GITHUB/SCRIPTS/GENERATE_XMIT.PY

  SEE SECTION 3 FOR A FULL EXPLANATION OF WHAT THIS SCRIPT DOES.
  OUTPUT FILE GSUK26V.XMIT IS WRITTEN TO THE REPOSITORY ROOT ON THE RUNNER.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 7 OF 7 - CREATE RELEASE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  ACTION  : SOFTPROPS/ACTION-GH-RELEASE@V2

  PUBLISHES A GITHUB RELEASE USING THE TAG FROM STEP 2/3.

  PARAMETERS:
    TAG_NAME  : THE AUTO-COMPUTED VERSION TAG (E.G. V1.3)
    NAME      : SAME AS TAG - USED AS THE RELEASE TITLE ON GITHUB
    BODY_PATH : GSUK26V.RELEASE  (THIS FILE - SHOWN AS RELEASE DESCRIPTION)
    FILES     : GSUK26V.XMIT     (ATTACHED AS DOWNLOADABLE RELEASE ASSET)

  AFTER THIS STEP THE RELEASE IS PUBLICLY VISIBLE ON GITHUB WITH THE XMIT
  FILE READY FOR DOWNLOAD.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                   3. SCRIPT: .GITHUB/SCRIPTS/GENERATE_XMIT.PY
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

LANGUAGE : PYTHON 3.11
LIBRARY  : XMI-READER (PIP INSTALL XMI-READER)

WHAT IT DOES:

  INPUT  : GSUK26V.PDS  (DIRECTORY REPRESENTING A PARTITIONED DATA SET)
  OUTPUT : GSUK26V.XMIT (STANDARD Z/OS XMIT / NETDATA FILE)

  CALLS CREATE_XMI() FROM THE XMI LIBRARY:
    FROM_USER : WIZARD
    FROM_NODE : GITHUB

THE PDS FOLDER CONTAINS ALL MEMBERS THAT WILL BE PACKAGED INTO THE XMIT.
EACH FILE IN THE FOLDER BECOMES A MEMBER OF THE PARTITIONED DATA SET.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                         4. RELEASE ASSETS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

EACH RELEASE CONTAINS ONE ASSET:

  GSUK26V.XMIT
    A STANDARD Z/OS NETDATA / XMIT FILE CONTAINING THE GSUK26V PDS.
    CAN BE RECEIVED ON Z/OS WITH THE RECEIVE COMMAND:
      TSO RECEIVE INDATASET('HLQ.GSUK26V.XMIT')
    OR OPENED LOCALLY WITH THE XMI-READER PYTHON LIBRARY.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                         5. VERSIONING SCHEME
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  V<MAJOR>.<MINOR>

  MINOR  : INCREMENTED AUTOMATICALLY ON EVERY PUSH TO MASTER
  MAJOR  : INCREMENTED MANUALLY BY PUSHING A NEW VMAJOR.0 TAG

  EXAMPLES:
    V1.0  -> INITIAL RELEASE (CREATED MANUALLY)
    V1.1  -> FIRST AUTO-BUILD AFTER V1.0
    V1.2  -> SECOND AUTO-BUILD
    V2.0  -> MANUALLY TRIGGERED MAJOR RELEASE
    V2.1  -> NEXT AUTO-BUILD AFTER V2.0

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                            :: END OF RELEASE NOTES ::
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
